Package edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.manager

Class TestPlanManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.manager.TestPlanManager
  • public class TestPlanManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A TestPlanManager has an ISortedList of TestPlans, one FailingTestList, an AbstractTestPlan for the currentTestPlan, and a boolean flag that keeps track of if the TestPlanManager has been changed since the last save.
    Author:
    Veerendra Gottiveeti, Yi Zhang

      • isChanged

        public boolean isChanged()
        Checks if there is an update between the current Test Plan and new Test Plan
        Returns:
        if the state if changed

      • addTestPlan

        public void addTestPlan​(java.lang.String testPlanName)
        Responsible for adding a test plan If the new TestPlan’s name is FAILING_TESTS_LIST_NAME or a duplicate of an existing TestPlan (both case insensitive), then an IAE is thrown with message “Invalid name.”. Otherwise, the TestPlan is added to the list of test plans, the current test plan is updated to the new test plan isChanged is updated to true.
        Parameters:
        testPlanName - Name of the test plan
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if parameter is null or empty string
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if test plan name is failing tests (case insensitive)
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if current test plan name is a duplicate of an existing TestPlan (case insensitive)

      • getTestPlanNames

        public java.lang.String[] getTestPlanNames()
        Returns a list of test plan names. The “Failing Tests” list is always listed first.
        Returns:
        a list of test plan names

      • editTestPlan

        public void editTestPlan​(java.lang.String testPlanName)
        Responsible for editing a specific test plan. When editing the currentTestPlan and you cannot edit the TestPlan in place in the ISortedList. isChanged is updated to true.
        Parameters:
        testPlanName - Name of the test plan
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the currentTestPlan is an FailingTestList
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the new name is Failing Tests (case insensitive)
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the new name is a duplicate of the name of an existing testPlan (case insensitive)

      • removeTestPlan

        public void removeTestPlan()
        Responsible for removing a test plan. isChanged is updated to true.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the current test plan is failing

      • addTestCase

        public void addTestCase​(TestCase t)
        A TestCase can only be added directly to a TestPlan. If the currentTestPlan is not a TestPlan do nothing with the TestCase. This is a place where the helper method getFailingTests() can be helpful. isChanged is updated to true.
        Parameters:
        t - Test case to be added

      • addTestResult

        public void addTestResult​(int idx,
                          boolean passing,
                          java.lang.String actualResult)
        Adds the test result to the test case at the given index in the current test plan. If the tests are failing, then the Failing Test List should be updated.
        Parameters:
        idx - Index of the current test plan
        passing - State of a test if it passes
        actualResult - Actual result of a test.

      • clearTestPlans

        public void clearTestPlans()
        Clears out the TestPlanManager by setting testPlans to an empty SortedList, failingTestList to an empty FailingTestList(), currentTestPlan to the failingTestList. isChanged to false.
